<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>If you have an Zend Form Submit Element translated when the user post the form,
Zend Form Submit Element try to translate the value posted not the Value assigned to it when it was Created</p>

<p>Sample:</p>

<h1>elenent was created with 'submit' =&gt; array('submit',array('value'=&gt;"submit2"))</h1>

<h1>it's value "submit2" was transated to let's say "Accept and Confirm"</h1>

<h1>user post the form</h1>

<h1>element try to translate "Accept and Confirm" not the "submit2"</h1>

    </div>
